  "body": "Hey guys,\n\nI know there are a lot of issues here so I'll try to make this quick and clear. The issue is that when you generate a sourcemap using the `react-tools` node module by calling `transformWithDetails(input, options)`, it will always output `source.js` in the `sources` property of the sourcemap that is generated, there is no way to specify the actual source file.\n\nI thought that perhaps the `sourceFilename` option would allow you to change this, but unfortunately it does not -- no matter what you set `sourceFilename` to, the `sources` property always returns as an array with `sources.js` in it only.\n\nA small snippet of code to quickly verify this:\n\n``` js\nvar jsx = require('react-tools'),\n    assert = require('assert');\n\nvar output = jsx.transformWithDetails(\"<div className='foo'></div>\", {\n  sourceMap: true,\n  sourceFilename: '/path/to/source.js'\n});\nvar test1 = assert.equal(output.sourceMap.sources.length, 1);\nvar test2 = assert.equal(output.sourceMap.sources[0], '/path/to/source.js');\n\nconsole.log(\"sources contains one entry: \" + test1);\nconsole.log(\"sources entry is correct: \" + test2);\n\n```\n",
